1) 	The CssResource-Interfaces are generated by the maven script.
	
	<plugin>
		<groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
		<artifactId>gwt-maven-plugin</artifactId>
		...
			<cssFiles>
				<cssFile>ch/kdev/todo/client/view/resources/AppStyleDesktop.css</cssFile>
			</cssFiles>
			<generateDirectory>${sourceDirectory}</generateDirectory>
		</configuration>
		<executions>
			<execution>
				<id>css-generation</id>
				<phase>generate-sources</phase>
				<goals>
					<goal>css</goal>
				</goals>
			</execution>
			...
		</executions>
	</plugin>


2) 	For each CssResource-Interface is a public Interface created which inherits from it.
	This is needed because the Interface-Generator only generates private CssResource-Interfaces.
	
	e.g. AppStyleDesktop.java --> AppStyleDesktopExt.java
	
	In the code is only the "Extension-Class" used.